Three brothers will appear at the Mbibane Magistrates’ Court in Mpumalanga today facing a charge of murder, Mpumalanga News reports.
This follows after the trio were arrested for allegedly beating to death a 36-year-old man, reported to be a brother of theirs, who they accused of being the sole beneficiary of their parents’ inheritance.
READ MORE: Man wanted for killing siblings
That, according to them, turned him into a rich man while they remained poor.
They reportedly assaulted him using their fists and bricks until he collapsed.
The trio then fled the scene while the victim was rushed to hospital where he was certified dead on arrival.
